\c 14  
\p
\v 1 Every wise woman buildeth her house: but the foolish plucketh it down with her hands. 
\v 2 He that walketh in his uprightness feareth the LORD: but \add he that is\add* perverse in his ways despiseth him. 
\v 3 In the mouth of the foolish \add is\add* a rod of pride: but the lips of the wise shall preserve them. 
\v 4 Where no oxen \add are\add* , the crib \add is\add* clean: but much increase \add is\add* by the strength of the ox. 
\v 5 A faithful witness will not lie: but a false witness will utter lies. 
\v 6 A scorner seeketh wisdom, and \add findeth it\add* not: but knowledge \add is\add* easy to him that understandeth. 
