\v 19 The evil bow before the good; and the wicked at the gates of the righteous. 
\v 20 The poor is hated even by his own neighbor: but the rich \add hath\add* many friends. 
\v 21 He that despiseth his neighbor sinneth: but he that hath mercy on the poor, happy \add is\add* he. 
