\v 31 The hoary head \add is\add* a crown of glory, \add if\add* it is found in the way of righteousness. 
\v 32  \add He that is\add* slow to anger \add is\add* better than the mighty; and he that ruleth his spirit, than he that taketh a city. 
\v 33 The lot is cast into the lap: but the whole disposing of it \add is\add* from the LORD. 
\c 17  
\p
\v 1 Better \add is\add* a dry morsel, and quietness with it, than a house full of sacrifices \add with\add* strife. 
