\c 19  
\p
\v 1 Better \add is\add* the poor that walketh in his integrity, than \add he that is\add* perverse in his lips, and is a fool. 
\v 2 Also, \add that\add* the soul \add be\add* without knowledge, \add it is\add* not good; and he that hasteth with \add his\add* feet sinneth. 
