\v 14 House and riches \add are\add* the inheritance of fathers: and a prudent wife \add is\add* from the LORD. 
\v 15 Slothfulness casteth into a deep sleep; and an idle soul shall suffer hunger. 
\v 16 He that keepeth the commandment keepeth his own soul; \add but\add* he that despiseth his ways shall die. 
\v 17 He that hath pity upon the poor, lendeth to the LORD; and that which he hath given will he pay him again. 
